WEBVTT

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.976
A few years ago,
I felt like I was stuck in a rut,

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:22.976
so I decided to follow in the footsteps

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.536
of the great American
philosopher, Morgan Spurlock,

00:00:26.560 --> 00:00:28.976
and try something new for 30 days.

00:00:29.523 --> 00:00:31.276
The idea is actually pretty simple.

00:00:31.675 --> 00:00:34.676
Think about something you've always
wanted to add to your life

00:00:34.700 --> 00:00:36.976
and try it for the next 30 days.

00:00:37.897 --> 00:00:41.291
It turns out 30 days is just
about the right amount of time

00:00:41.315 --> 00:00:44.007
to add a new habit or subtract a habit --

00:00:44.031 --> 00:00:45.276
like watching the news --

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:46.976
from your life.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.191
There's a few things I learned
while doing these 30-day challenges.

00:00:50.622 --> 00:00:51.976
The first was,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.976
instead of the months
flying by, forgotten,

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:57.976
the time was much more memorable.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:01.572
This was part of a challenge I did
to take a picture every day for a month.

00:01:01.596 --> 00:01:06.021
And I remember exactly where I was
and what I was doing that day.

00:01:07.132 --> 00:01:08.409
I also noticed

00:01:08.433 --> 00:01:11.762
that as I started to do more
and harder 30-day challenges,

00:01:11.786 --> 00:01:12.976
my self-confidence grew.

00:01:13.579 --> 00:01:15.476
I went from desk-dwelling computer nerd

00:01:15.500 --> 00:01:17.976
to the kind of guy who bikes to work.

00:01:18.597 --> 00:01:19.845
For fun!

00:01:19.869 --> 00:01:21.219
(Laughter)

00:01:21.243 --> 00:01:24.266
Even last year, I ended up hiking
up Mt. Kilimanjaro,

00:01:24.290 --> 00:01:25.976
the highest mountain in Africa.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:31.023
I would never have been that adventurous
before I started my 30-day challenges.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.597
I also figured out that if you
really want something badly enough,

00:01:36.621 --> 00:01:38.976
you can do anything for 30 days.

00:01:40.105 --> 00:01:41.970
Have you ever wanted to write a novel?

00:01:42.959 --> 00:01:44.250
Every November,

00:01:44.274 --> 00:01:45.576
tens of thousands of people

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:49.681
try to write their own
50,000-word novel, from scratch,

00:01:49.705 --> 00:01:50.976
in 30 days.

00:01:51.663 --> 00:01:56.512
It turns out, all you have to do
is write 1,667 words a day

00:01:56.536 --> 00:01:57.739
for a month.

00:01:58.573 --> 00:01:59.976
So I did.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.861
By the way, the secret
is not to go to sleep

00:02:02.885 --> 00:02:04.982
until you've written
your words for the day.

00:02:05.530 --> 00:02:06.976
You might be sleep-deprived,

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:08.698
but you'll finish your novel.

00:02:09.769 --> 00:02:12.976
Now is my book the next great
American novel?

00:02:13.447 --> 00:02:14.976
No. I wrote it in a month.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.836
It's awful.

00:02:16.860 --> 00:02:18.502
(Laughter)

00:02:18.526 --> 00:02:20.711
But for the rest of my life,

00:02:20.735 --> 00:02:22.976
if I meet John Hodgman at a TED party,

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:24.976
I don't have to say,

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:26.976
"I'm a computer scientist."

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.339
No, no, if I want to,
I can say, "I'm a novelist."

00:02:30.363 --> 00:02:33.725
(Laughter)

00:02:33.749 --> 00:02:35.976
So here's one last thing
I'd like to mention.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.479
I learned that when I made
small, sustainable changes,

00:02:39.503 --> 00:02:40.976
things I could keep doing,

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:43.223
they were more likely to stick.

00:02:43.247 --> 00:02:45.976
There's nothing wrong
with big, crazy challenges.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.366
In fact, they're a ton of fun.

00:02:48.828 --> 00:02:50.430
But they're less likely to stick.

00:02:51.250 --> 00:02:53.818
When I gave up sugar for 30 days,

00:02:53.842 --> 00:02:55.657
day 31 looked like this.

00:02:55.681 --> 00:02:57.985
(Laughter)

00:02:58.009 --> 00:03:00.450
So here's my question to you:

00:03:00.474 --> 00:03:02.209
What are you waiting for?

00:03:02.233 --> 00:03:04.511
I guarantee you the next 30 days

00:03:04.535 --> 00:03:08.135
are going to pass
whether you like it or not,

00:03:08.159 --> 00:03:12.858
so why not think about something
you have always wanted to try

00:03:12.882 --> 00:03:14.129
and give it a shot!

00:03:14.711 --> 00:03:16.060
For the next 30 days.

00:03:16.656 --> 00:03:17.976
Thanks.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:21.880
(Applause)